    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-06T15:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-06T15:45:00-05:00" n="663"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-06T15:00:00-05:45"
                            >May 6, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. President Moncada has re-submitted the Honduras-Nicaraguan boundary protocol
                    (the documents of the original submission having <pb facs="0916" n="802"
                        xml:id="pg_802"/> been destroyed in the recent fire) to the Nicaraguan
                    Congress and there is a chance that it will be approved in the few remaining
                    days of the session.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
